HEADWORD: affixed
<hw>affixed</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>attached physically.
Opposite of <ant>unaffixed</ant>.</def> <note>Various more specific
adjectives meaning affixed are: <stype>appendant </stype>,
<stype>basifixed</stype>, <stype>fastened, secured</stype>,
<stype>glued, pasted, stuck to(predicate) </stype>, <stype>pegged-down
</stype>, <stype>pinned, stapled </stype>, <stype>taped
to(predicate)</stype>, <stype>mounted </stype>.</note>⟦br⟧
